item.title: Jenell add a quote by Truman Capote
item.description: "But you can't give your heart to a wild thing: the more you do the stronger they get. Until they're strong enough to run into the woods. Or fly into a tree. Then a taller tree. Then the sky. That's how you'll end up Mr. Bell. If you let yourself love a wild thing. You'll end up looking at the sky." -- Truman Capote

item.title: Jenell add a quote by Marguerite Duras
